<subSubSection id="9C8B6553FFDCBB4A2FA529BD0A7DF9AB" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D42E36D8FFDCBB4A2FA529BD0A7DF9AB" blockId="12.[151,1437,1438,1789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2FA529BD083BFA53" bold="true" box="[151,305,1474,1500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">Distribution.</emphasis>
Atlanto-Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFDCBB4A2D7829BD0A93FA53" author="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S." box="[586,921,1474,1500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" pagination="273 - 292" refId="ref18519" refString="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S. (2003) Biogeography of benthic marine amphipods in Mediterranean Sea. Biogeographia-The Journal of Integrative Biogeography, 24 (1), 273 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.21426 / B 6110176" type="journal article" year="2003">Bellan-Santini &amp; Ruffo 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFDCBB4A2C9529BD0DC5FA53" author="Christodoulou, M. &amp; Paraskevopoulou, S. &amp; Syranidou, E. &amp; Koukouras, A." box="[935,1231,1474,1500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" pagination="1303 - 1327" refId="ref19520" refString="Christodoulou, M., Paraskevopoulou, S., Syranidou, E. &amp; Koukouras, A. (2013) The amphipod (Crustacea: Peracarida) fauna of the Aegean Sea, and comparison with those of the neighbouring seas. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 93 (5), 1303 - 1327. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 002531541200183 X" type="journal article" year="2013">
Christodoulou 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2B6229BC0D80FA53" box="[1104,1162,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). The species was reported from 
<collectingCountry id="AC867648FFDCBB4A2E5B299908B0F98F" box="[361,442,1510,1536]" name="Cyprus" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFDCBB4A2ED629980B77F98F" author="Russo, A. R." box="[484,637,1510,1537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" pagination="169 - 179" refId="ref23615" refString="Russo, A. R. (1997) Epifauna living on sublittoral seaweeds around Cyprus. Hydrobiologia, 344, 169 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1002970714963" type="journal article" year="1997">Russo (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFDCBB4A2DBB29980A7CF98F" author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[649,886,1510,1537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2DD929980A2EF98F" box="[747,804,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFDCBB4A2C9F29990DE8F98F" author="Christodoulou, M. &amp; Paraskevopoulou, S. &amp; Syranidou, E. &amp; Koukouras, A." box="[941,1250,1510,1536]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" pagination="1303 - 1327" refId="ref19520" refString="Christodoulou, M., Paraskevopoulou, S., Syranidou, E. &amp; Koukouras, A. (2013) The amphipod (Crustacea: Peracarida) fauna of the Aegean Sea, and comparison with those of the neighbouring seas. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 93 (5), 1303 - 1327. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 002531541200183 X" type="journal article" year="2013">
Christodoulou 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2B6729980D87F98F" box="[1109,1165,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
. In Vasiliko Bay (current study), it is considered as a rare species (FI: 7.14 %).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C8B6553FFDCBB4A2FA52A5108B2F972" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D42E36D8FFDCBB4A2FA52A5108B2F972" blockId="12.[151,1437,1438,1789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2FA52A5109F6F9C7" bold="true" box="[151,252,1582,1608]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFDCBB4A2E312A5008C7F9C7" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1830" box="[259,461,1583,1608]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Lysianassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costae">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2E312A5008C7F9C7" box="[259,461,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">Lysianassa costae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in association with algae, on rocks and stones and in soft-bottom sediments (mud, mud-and mixture) at 
<quantity id="13699B3DFFDCBB4A2D312A2D0B62F9E2" box="[515,616,1618,1645]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" unit="m" value="75.5" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="1.0">1–150 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFDCBB4A2D8D2A2D0AABF9E3" author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[703,929,1618,1644]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2C162A2C0A54F9E3" box="[804,862,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFDCBB4A2C9D2A2D0DDDF9E3" author="Christodoulou, M. &amp; Paraskevopoulou, S. &amp; Syranidou, E. &amp; Koukouras, A." box="[943,1239,1618,1644]" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" pagination="1303 - 1327" refId="ref19520" refString="Christodoulou, M., Paraskevopoulou, S., Syranidou, E. &amp; Koukouras, A. (2013) The amphipod (Crustacea: Peracarida) fauna of the Aegean Sea, and comparison with those of the neighbouring seas. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 93 (5), 1303 - 1327. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 002531541200183 X" type="journal article" year="2013">
Christodoulou 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2B6A2A2C0D98F9E3" box="[1112,1170,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). In Vasiliko Bay it was found at depths of 
<quantity id="13699B3DFFDCBB4A2EDB2A090B47F91E" box="[489,589,1654,1681]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" unit="m" value="27.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="20.0">20–35 m</quantity>
(29 + 
<quantity id="13699B3DFFDCBB4A2DA92A090BC0F91E" box="[667,714,1654,1681]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" unit="m" value="8.0">8 m</quantity>
), in muddy sand substrate with organic matter ranging between 
<geoCoordinate id="B1A5501FFFDCBB4A2FF42AE5080FF93A" box="[198,261,1690,1717]" degrees="6.265" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" precision="55" value="6.265">6.265</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="B1A5501FFFDCBB4A2E362AE50858F93A" box="[260,338,1690,1717]" degrees="8.416" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" precision="55" value="-8.416">–8.416</geoCoordinate>
% (7.459 + 1.095 %) and in association with 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2C6B2AE40D9BF93B" box="[857,1169,1690,1717]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFDCBB4A2C6B2AE40AEAF93B" authorityName="J. V. Lamouroux" authorityYear="1809" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" box="[857,992,1690,1717]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="prolifera">C. prolifera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFDCBB4A2CD92AE40D9BF93B" authorityName="Sonder" authorityYear="1845" box="[1003,1169,1690,1717]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="cylindracea">C. cylindracea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFDCBB4A2BFA2AE40C43F93B" authorityName="Delile" authorityYear="1813" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[1224,1353,1691,1716]" class="Liliopsida" family="Posidoniaceae" genus="Posidonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="12" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oceanica">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFDCBB4A2BFA2AE40C43F93B" box="[1224,1353,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="385">P. oceanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was found in stations classified as “moderate” according to the Bentix Index. It was also recorded at a fish farm station (1 individual).
</paragraph>
